{
  "texts": [
    "The average number of input tokens per note was substantially less in CLEAR compared to chunk embedding and full note.",
    "On average, CLEAR had 81% fewer input tokens than the full-note approach and 71% fewer input tokens than chunk embedding (Fig. 2b -d and Supplementary Table 12).",
    "We estimated the time required for human evaluators to extract the same information from the training data by recording how long it took our domain expert to annotate 100 notes.",
    "On average, it took 57 s for a human to annotate one variable in a clinical note, which would result in approximately 3299 h to complete the annotation of 13 variables in",
    "16,031 notes."
  ]
}